[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDuring fuzz testing of libxml2’s HTML parser, AddressSanitizer detected a [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow in the function UTF32ToUTF8 [0m[1;39m([0m[39mencoding.[0m[1;92mc:2868[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. A one-byte [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwrite is occurring just past the end of a [0m[1;36m6001[0m[39m-byte heap buffer that was allocated [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor character conversion. The overflow is triggered when parsing a specially [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcrafted HTML input under the libFuzzer harness.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIssue:[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A heap-buffer-overflow is reported by AddressSanitizer at UTF32ToUTF8 in [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibxml2’s encoding.c [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m2868[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The error is a [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte out-of-bounds write immediately after a [0m[1;36m6001[0m[39m-byte [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocation region.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mVulnerability Type:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Heap buffer overflow [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSCARINESS: [0m[1;36m31[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbeyond the end of the output buffer. [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch attempt modifies the surrogate-pair handling in UTF32ToUTF8: it adds a [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbounds check [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39moutend - out[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m < [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m break;`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and restores the original four-byte[0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The initial issue is an AddressSanitizer–reported heap-buffer-overflow in [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibxml2’s UTF32ToUTF8 function [0m[1;39m([0m[39mencoding.[0m[1;92mc:2868[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A patch was attempted that:[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Introduced an `outend` pointer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`out + *outlen`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Added a bounds check before emitting a [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte surrogate pair,  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Restored correct UTF-[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m encoding for code points assembled from surrogate pairs.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After applying the patch, the same heap-buffer-overflow still occurs at [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mencoding.c [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnow line [0m[1;36m2869[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, indicating the new check does not prevent the overflow [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min all cases.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - During fuzz testing of the HTML parser, AddressSanitizer reports a one-byte [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwrite just past the end of a buffer allocated by `xmlFuzzMalloc`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`xmlBufCreate`.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The failure occurs in `UTF32ToUTF8` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mencoding.[0m[1;92mc:2868[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, called by [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlEncInputChunk` → `xmlCharEncInput` → `xmlParserInputBufferGrow` → HTML parsing [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunctions.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow is triggered when converting UTF-[0m[1;36m32[0m[39m surrogate pairs into UTF-[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwriting one byte beyond the allocated region.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Key Observations from the ASan Log  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow address equals `outstart + *outlen`: it is exactly one byte past [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe permitted buffer end.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The buggy write is a single byte of the UTF-[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m sequence, at the final `[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m3[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindex of a four-byte sequence.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The heap allocation was [0m[1;36m6001[0m[39m bytes, and the code attempts to write at offset [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6001[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mout of [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m6000[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The call stack climbs from the fuzzer harness into HTML parsing internals and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdown into encoding conversion routines.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `UTF32ToUTF8` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround original line [0m[1;36m2846[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the patch:  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Declares `unsigned char *outend = out + *outlen;`  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Before emitting a [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte sequence for a surrogate pair, checks `if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39moutend [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- out[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m < [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m break;`  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Restores the correct calculation of `c` and UTF-[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m bit patterns.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The patched code places the surrogate combination and bounds check inside the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrelevant branch, then advances `in` and `out`.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Patch Result and Reproduction Log  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A new ASan report shows an overflow at encoding.[0m[1;92mc:2869[0m[39m, in the same function, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicating the guard did not prevent writing past `outend`.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The reproduction command and stack trace mirror the original, except the code [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moffsets have shifted by one line.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow remains a write of size [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m at the exact boundary.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Buffer sizing logic in `xmlEncInputChunk` [0m[35m/[0m[39m `xmlCharEncInput` – verify how [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`*outlen` is initialized and updated.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overall contract of `UTF32ToUTF8`: whether it assumes a minimum free space[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor grows its output buffer.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How surrogate pairs are detected and dispatched vs. single‐code‐unit paths [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m3[0m[39m byte UTF-[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m sequences[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Interaction with `xmlParserGrow` [0m[35m/[0m[39m `xmlParserInputBufferGrow` and HTML parser [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minternals [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`htmlParseCharData`, `xmlDetectEncoding`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any other code paths in encoding.c that encode multi-byte sequences and may [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlack similar bounds checks.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer heap-buffer-overflow was detected in libxml2’s UTF32ToUTF8 [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconversion during HTML parsing under fuzzing. The crash trace shows a one-byte [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwrite past the end of a heap buffer in encoding.[0m[1;92mc:2868[0m[39m. A patch was attempted to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreplace the converter callback in xmlEncInputChunk with a call to UTF32ToUTF8 that [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmanually tracks buffer availability and to add explicit boundary checks in [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mUTF32ToUTF8. When the patch was applied, the build failed with multiple “use of [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mundeclared identifier” and “expected expression” errors, indicating the patch was [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmis-scoped or missing required context [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., missing declarations of `buf`, `use`,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`avail`, `outend` and incorrect bracing[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Fuzzing invocation: `run_fuzzer html -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m [0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m`.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Crash location: AddressSanitizer reports a heap-buffer-overflow at UTF32ToUTF8[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min encoding.c. The write of size [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m occurs at the end of a [0m[1;36m6001[0m[39m-byte region.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Call stack highlights xmlEncInputChunk → xmlCharEncInput → [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlParserInputBufferGrow → htmlParseCharData → htmlParseContent → htmlParseDocument[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m→ fuzzer entrypoint.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow happens because UTF32ToUTF8 writes one byte beyond the allocated [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In xmlEncInputChunk [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m1480[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the handler-based call was removed and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreplaced with:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Computation of `use = [0m[1;35mxmlBufUse[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `avail = [0m[1;35mxmlBufAvail[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • A direct call to `[0m[1;35mUTF32ToUTF8[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mxmlBufContent[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + use, &avail, in, &ilen[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • A subsequent `[0m[1;35mxmlBufAdd[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf, [0m[1;35mxmlBufContent[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + use, avail[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In UTF32ToUTF8 [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m2846[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, a new pointer `outend = out + *outlen;` was[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mintroduced, and before emitting each code-unit sequence [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the code [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks `[0m[1;39m([0m[39moutend – out[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m < N` and breaks if insufficient space. The surrogate [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhandling was consolidated into a canonical [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte UTF-[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m encoding.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Result  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Compilation errors in encoding.c:  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • xmlEncInputChunk: `use`, `buf`, `avail`, `ilen` are undeclared.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • UTF32ToUTF8: syntax errors [0m[1;39m([0m[39m“expected expression”, mismatched braces[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m around[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe newly added `else [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` blocks.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • One unused-parameter warning on `out` in xmlEncInputChunk.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The errors indicate that the patch context [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., variable declarations, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction signatures, surrounding braces[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m was incorrect or incomplete.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhandling in xmlEncInputChunk. Verify that `xmlEncInputChunk` has access to an [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlBufPtr` and the names of its variables.  [0m                                       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnesting.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Interaction between xmlBuf functions [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`xmlBufUse`, `xmlBufAvail`, [0m             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How xmlEncInputChunk is called and what the existing `handler->input` contract[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhat preconditions exist on `out`, `outlen`, and `inlen`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                      [2m                [0m
